191
00:18:33,186 --> 00:18:42,749
[SPEAKER_01]: And the notice requirement under the open meeting law doesn't substitute or supersede any other notice requirements if you have them under any other legal requirements.

192
00:18:43,209 --> 00:18:49,471
[SPEAKER_01]: So always worth double checking to make sure you're covering any publication notice or anything else that may be required.

193
00:18:51,852 --> 00:18:52,732
[SPEAKER_01]: Emergencies.

194
00:18:52,752 --> 00:18:59,754
[SPEAKER_01]: I can't tell you how many questions I get regarding emergencies, particularly in the winter months with inclement weather.

195
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:09,191
[SPEAKER_01]: There are very limited instances when a public body can meet without that 48 hours notice that's required.

196
00:19:09,211 --> 00:19:16,554
[SPEAKER_01]: Floor planning doesn't equal an emergency, we know from determinations of the Attorney General's office.

