206
00:20:33,166 --> 00:20:40,471
[SPEAKER_01]: So we're going to move a little bit from the notice piece of this and the agenda piece of the open meeting law to now how those meetings are conducted.

207
00:20:40,491 --> 00:20:51,260
[SPEAKER_01]: These are topics that I often receive a lot of questions about, so I just wanted to make sure everyone had the best practices related to these particular topics of the open meeting law.

208
00:20:52,280 --> 00:21:08,690
[SPEAKER_01]: We know that if the meeting is being recorded, similar to whether it be on Zoom or in person, that there should be a public statement or notification to the public through the technological means that the meeting minute is going to be recorded.

209
00:21:08,710 --> 00:21:12,813
[SPEAKER_01]: And the basis of that is the Massachusetts wiretap statute.

210
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:16,175
[SPEAKER_01]: We can't secretly record anyone in Massachusetts.

211
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:22,853
[SPEAKER_01]: If an individual wants to record the meeting on their own, it's not otherwise recorded.

212
00:21:22,913 --> 00:21:34,518
[SPEAKER_01]: So if someone shows up to an in-person meeting, it used to be when I started doing this, it would be the big recording device with a tripod that we had the old VCR tapes for.

