00:25:21,079 --> 00:25:21,719
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay, great.

245
00:25:22,079 --> 00:25:22,460
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

246
00:25:23,615 --> 00:25:29,196
[SPEAKER_01]: Texting and social media, texting and social media, similar, also subject to the open meeting law.

247
00:25:29,676 --> 00:25:38,258
[SPEAKER_01]: Facebook, Snapchat, Twitter, Reddit, all of those are subject to the public records law and the open meeting law to the extent there is deliberation.

248
00:25:39,698 --> 00:25:47,140
[SPEAKER_01]: If you are a user of social media, certainly in your individual capacity, you have free speech and first amendment considerations.

249
00:25:48,011 --> 00:25:53,392
[SPEAKER_01]: So I'm not going to speak directly to your individual rights, but certainly some practical approaches.

250
00:25:53,492 --> 00:25:59,074
[SPEAKER_01]: If you are posting on your service, you don't want to direct comments to your other members.

