00:27:40,465 --> 00:27:45,308
[SPEAKER_01]: all of the decisions as to who's going to speak or for how long should be content neutral.

263
00:27:45,368 --> 00:27:53,352
[SPEAKER_01]: So not based on the particular message for a speaker or what that individual says, but just based on the time that's allotted.

264
00:27:54,593 --> 00:28:00,096
[SPEAKER_01]: Some public bodies I work with say 15 minutes of public comment, everyone gets two or three minutes.

265
00:28:00,649 --> 00:28:05,293
[SPEAKER_01]: People are allowed to speak once or twice, depending on how busy the agenda is.

266
00:28:06,314 --> 00:28:09,337
[SPEAKER_01]: And some have adopted public comment policies as well.

267
00:28:09,417 --> 00:28:13,100
[SPEAKER_01]: So certainly something to put out there to all of you to consider.

268
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:22,428
[SPEAKER_01]: And we'll talk a little bit more about public comment, but the chair does have the authority to regulate it subject to those constitutional restrictions.

269
00:28:26,113 --> 00:28:33,816
[SPEAKER_01]: Public participation, whether or not to allow public participation is a significant policy decision.

